# Grievance Module (Phase 2+)

**Do not implement until Phase 1 auth shell, MFA, and audit log exist.**

## Confidentiality
- MFA required for all grievance access
- Immutable audit log on every view and edit
- No PII in application logs or error trackers
- Member identity: pseudonym option; encrypt real names at rest

## Data Rules
- Every query scoped by `unionId` + `localId`
- Stewards see only assigned cases unless elevated role
- CA steps and deadlines from `CAConfig` — never hardcoded OPSEU steps
- Email drafts only — never auto-send without steward review

## Features Reference
See `docs/modules/GRIEVANCE.md` and `docs/COMPLIANCE.md`.

## Do Not
- Build grievance CRUD in Phase 0 or without auth
- Cross-local or cross-union grievance queries
- Store attachments without virus scan (Phase 2+)
